i deleted my linked-in a few years ago. haven't felt regret since. i saw a random tweet, i think from a dev at opencode, that said the best thing you can do for your career development is to get away from linkedin. lol.

random thought on llms:

* i have run into reasoning constraints even with claude opus 4.6 (current SOTA model)
* i find they cannot speed up thinking/designing a solution
* however they are fantastic for getting ballpark estimates
* llms are great for throwaway code and unimportant grunt work

i don't have negative views with llms. i was a little scared at the beginning. i'm imagining a future 10 years for now where we have starwars like R2D2s and C3POs, where they are close to human, but not quite there and still have their little quirks.

